sentences: Noah Gundersen (born May 31, 1989) is an American indie folk singer-songwriter from Seattle.
In 2008, Gundersen produced his first EP, Brand New World.
In 2008, Gundersen collaborated with friends and his then-16-year-old sister to form the band The Courage.
The group later recorded a live album, Live at the Triple Door, under the name Noah Gundersen & The Courage in 2008.
The band performed at the Sisters Folk Festival in both 2008 and 2010 and evolved further, recording their debut album, Fearful Bones, under the name The Courage in 2010.
